# UI Fingerprint (`crates/server/ui.lock`)

The bundled UI lives under `node/`, outside the `olai-uc-server` crate tree.
`crates/server/ui.lock` fingerprints every tracked file under `node/` so release-plz
ties UI changes to the server crate and triggers a Docker image rebuild.

## Before Creating Any PR

If you changed anything under `node/`, regenerate and commit the lock:

```bash
just ui-fingerprint
```

Verify locally (same check CI runs):

```bash
just ui-fingerprint-check
```

## What Not To Do

- **Never hand-edit** `crates/server/ui.lock`.
- Do not open a PR with `node/` changes and a stale `ui.lock` — CI's
  `ui-fingerprint` job will fail.

## Pre-commit Hook

When any staged file is under `node/` or `crates/server/ui.lock` is staged, the
repo pre-commit hook (`.githooks/pre-commit`):

1. Regenerates `ui.lock` when `node/` files are staged.
2. Runs `just ui-fingerprint-check` and aborts the commit if the lock is still stale.

Activate once per clone:

```bash
bun run setup-hooks   # git config core.hooksPath .githooks
```

The hook is a safety net — still run `just ui-fingerprint-check` before opening a PR.

## After merging `main`

Merging `main` into a feature branch often conflicts on `ui.lock` because both
branches changed `node/`. **Do not keep either side's hash** — regenerate from the
merged tree:

```bash
git fetch origin main
git merge origin/main
# if ui.lock conflicts: remove conflict markers, then:
just ui-fingerprint
git add crates/server/ui.lock
git commit   # complete the merge, or amend the merge commit
just ui-fingerprint-check
```

Agents resolving a `main` merge should always run `just ui-fingerprint` before
finishing the merge commit.

## Post-merge hook

After a merge or pull that changes `node/`, [`.githooks/post-merge`](../../.githooks/post-merge)
runs `just ui-fingerprint-check` and regenerates `ui.lock` when stale. If the lock
file changes, commit it in a follow-up (or amend the merge commit before pushing).

Activated with the other repo hooks: `bun run setup-hooks`.
